def get_article_links(base_url, n_articles=50):
    articles = [] # Menyimpan link artikel yang ditemukan
    page = 1 # Mulai dari halaman pertama

    while len(articles) < n_articles:
        # Tambahkan parameter halaman ke URL
        url = f"{base_url}page/{page}/" # Tambahkan nomor halaman ke URL
        response = requests.get(url) # Ambil konten halaman
        soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser') # Parsing HTML

        # Ambil semua artikel pada halaman tersebut
        for article in soup.find_all('article'):
            link = article.find('a', href=True)['href'] # Ambil link artikel
            articles.append(link) # Simpan link di list articles

            # Berhenti jika sudah mendapatkan n_articles
            if len(articles) >= n_articles:
                break # Jika sudah cukup, hentikan

        # Jika tidak ada artikel lagi di halaman, hentikan loop
        if not soup.find_all('article'):
            break # Jika tidak ada artikel lagi, hentikan loop

        # Lanjutkan ke halaman berikutnya
        page += 1 # Lanjut ke halaman berikutnya

    return articles[:n_articles]

def get_article_details(article_url):
    response = requests.get(article_url) # Ambil halaman artikel
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')

    # Extract title
    title = soup.find('h1', class_='entry-title').get_text(strip=True)

    # Extract date
    date = soup.find('time', class_='entry-date').get_text(strip=True)

    # Extract content
    content = soup.find('div', class_='entry-content').get_text(strip=True)

    # Extract category
    category = soup.find('span', class_='cat-links-content').get_text(strip=True)

    return title, date, content, category

# Mengambil dan Menyimpan Data dari Dua Kategori
# URLs for categories Nasional and Jombangku
url_nasional = 'https://wargajombang.com/category/nasional/'
url_jombangku = 'https://wargajombang.com/category/jombangku/'

# Get 50 articles from each category, navigating through multiple pages
article_links_nasional = get_article_links(url_nasional, n_articles=50)
article_links_jombangku = get_article_links(url_jombangku, n_articles=50)

# List kosong untuk menyimpan data artikel
articles_data = []

# Crawl Nasional category articles
for link in article_links_nasional:
    title, date, content, category = get_article_details(link)
    articles_data.append({
        'Title': title,
        'Date': date,

# Crawl Jombangku category articles

        'Content': content,
        'Category': category
    })

import re
import pandas as pd
import nltk
import string

def remove_url(text):
    #Fungsi untuk menghapus URL dari teks.
    url = re.compile(r'https?://\S+|www\.\S+')
    return url.sub(r'', text)

def remove_html(text):
    #Fungsi untuk menghapus tag HTML dari teks.
    html = re.compile(r'<.*?>')
    return html.sub(r'', text)

def remove_emoji(text):

    #Fungsi untuk menghapus emoji dari teks.
    emoji_pattern = re.compile("["
        u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"  # emotikon wajah
        u"\U0001F300-\U0001F5FF"  # simbol & gambar
        u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"  # transportasi & simbol
        u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"  # bendera negara
        "]+", flags=re.UNICODE)
    return emoji_pattern.sub(r'', text)

def remove_numbers(text):
    #Fungsi untuk menghapus angka dari teks.
    return re.sub(r'\d+', '', text)

def remove_symbols(text):
    #Fungsi untuk menghapus simbol dan karakter khusus dari teks.
    return re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9\s]', '', text)

# Asumsikan df adalah DataFrame yang berisi data Warga Jombang (judul, berita, tanggal, kategori)

# Terapkan fungsi cleansing untuk kolom 'berita'
df['berita_clean'] = df['Content'].apply(remove_url)
df['berita_clean'] = df['berita_clean'].apply(remove_html)
df['berita_clean'] = df['berita_clean'].apply(remove_emoji)
df['berita_clean'] = df['berita_clean'].apply(remove_symbols)
df['berita_clean'] = df['berita_clean'].apply(remove_numbers)

import numpy as np
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense

# 1. Dataset sederhana
corpus = ["saya suka makan nasi", "saya suka belajar python", "nasi adalah makanan pokok"]

# 2. Preprocessing - Membuat dictionary dari kata-kata
vocab = set(" ".join(corpus).split())  # Mengambil semua kata unik
vocab_size = len(vocab)  # Jumlah kata dalam vocab
word_index = {word: i for i, word in enumerate(vocab)}  # Mapping kata ke indeks

# Fungsi untuk membuat one-hot encoding
def one_hot_encode(word, vocab_size):
    one_hot = np.zeros(vocab_size) # Membuat vektor nol dengan panjang vocab_size
    one_hot[word_index[word]] = 1 # Mengisi indeks kata dengan 1
    return one_hot

# 3. Membuat pasangan skipgram (kata target, kata konteks)
def generate_skipgram_pairs(corpus, window_size=2):
    skipgram_pairs = []
    for sentence in corpus:
        words = sentence.split() # Tokenisasi kalimat
        for i, target_word in enumerate(words):
            context_words = words[max(0, i - window_size): min(len(words), i + window_size + 1)]
            context_words.remove(target_word) # Hilangkan kata target dari konteks
            for context_word in context_words:
                skipgram_pairs.append((target_word, context_word))
    return skipgram_pairs

skipgram_pairs = generate_skipgram_pairs(corpus)

# 4. Menyiapkan data untuk training - input (target word) dan label (context word)
X_train = np.array([one_hot_encode(pair[0], vocab_size) for pair in skipgram_pairs])
y_train = np.array([one_hot_encode(pair[1], vocab_size) for pair in skipgram_pairs])

# 5. Membangun model jaringan syaraf tiruan dengan representasi vektor 3 elemen
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(3, input_dim=vocab_size, activation='linear'))  # Hidden layer dengan output vektor berukuran 3
model.add(Dense(vocab_size, activation='softmax'))  # Output layer untuk prediksi kata konteks

# 6. Compile model
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy')

# 7. Training model
model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=100)

# 8. Mendapatkan embedding kata dalam bentuk vektor 3 elemen
word_embeddings = model.layers[0].get_weights()[0]

# Menampilkan embedding untuk setiap kata
for word, idx in word_index.items():
    print(f"Word: {word}, Embedding: {word_embeddings[idx]}")

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import csv

# URL dari artikel sepak bola di IDN Times
url = 'https://wargajombang.com/pembukaan-jombang-fest-2024-dihadiri-sejumlah-pejabat-pemerintahan-dari-berbagai-daerah/'

# Membuat permintaan ke URL
response = requests.get(url)

# Inisialisasi data yang akan disimpan
# Mengambil ulang dan membersihkan data yang diminta
artikel_jbg = []

if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parsing halaman web
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')

    # Mengambil judul artikel
    title = soup.find('h1').get_text().strip()

    # Mengambil tanggal publikasi artikel dan membersihkan spasi berlebih
    date = soup.find('time').get_text().strip()

    # Mengambil isi artikel dengan membersihkan konten tambahan
    content = soup.find_all('p')
    article_text = '\n'.join([p.get_text().strip() for p in content if p.get_text().strip()])

    # Simpan data dalam bentuk dictionary yang telah dibersihkan
    artikel_jbg.append({
        'Title': title,
        'Date': date,
        'Content': article_text
    })

# Membuat dataframe dari data yang telah dibersihkan
data_jbg = pd.DataFrame(artikel_jbg)

# Menampilkan dataframe yang bersih
data_jbg

# Proses case folding
def casefolding(Content):
    if isinstance(Content, list):
        # Jika Content adalah list, terapkan case folding pada setiap elemen
        return [str(item).lower() for item in Content]
    else:
        # Jika Content adalah string, langsung terapkan case folding
        return str(Content).lower()

# Terapkan fungsi casefolding pada kolom 'Content'
data_jbg['Content'] = data_jbg['Content'].apply(casefolding)

def cleansing(Content):
    # Menghapus whitespace di awal dan akhir teks
    Content = Content.strip()

    # Menghapus tanda baca dan karakter khusus
    Content = re.sub(f"[{string.punctuation}]", '', Content)

    # Menghapus angka
    Content = re.sub(r'\d+', '', Content)

    # Menghapus huruf tunggal (opsional, tergantung kebutuhan)
    Content = re.sub(r"\b[a-zA-Z]\b", "", Content)

    # Menghapus karakter-karakter non-standar seperti â
    Content = re.sub(r'[^\x00-\x7F]+', '', Content)

    # Menghapus spasi ganda
    Content = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', Content)

    return Content

# Terapkan fungsi cleansing pada kolom 'Content'
data_jbg['Content'] = data_jbg['Content'].apply(cleansing)

import pandas as pd
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
from nltk.tokenize import sent_tokenize, word_tokenize

# Assuming we have the article_text
sentences = sent_tokenize(article_text)
terms_per_sentence = [word_tokenize(sentence) for sentence in sentences]
extracted_terms = [{'Sentence': sentence, 'Terms': terms} for sentence, terms in zip(sentences, terms_per_sentence)]
df_terms = pd.DataFrame(extracted_terms)

# Menggabungkan terms menjadi string untuk setiap kalimat
df_terms['Terms_String'] = df_terms['Terms'].apply(' '.join)

# Membuat TF-IDF Vectorizer
tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()

# Fit dan transform data
tfidf_matrix = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(df_terms['Terms_String'])

# Mendapatkan nama-nama feature (terms)
feature_names = tfidf_vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()

# Membuat DataFrame untuk nilai TF-IDF
tfidf_df = pd.DataFrame(tfidf_matrix.toarray(), columns=feature_names)

# Menambahkan kolom Sentence
tfidf_df['Sentence'] = df_terms['Sentence']

# Melelehkan (melting) DataFrame untuk format yang lebih mudah dibaca
melted_tfidf = tfidf_df.melt(id_vars=['Sentence'], var_name='Term', value_name='TF-IDF')

# Menghapus baris dengan nilai TF-IDF 0
melted_tfidf = melted_tfidf[melted_tfidf['TF-IDF'] != 0]

# Mengurutkan berdasarkan nilai TF-IDF tertinggi
melted_tfidf = melted_tfidf.sort_values('TF-IDF', ascending=False)

# Menampilkan hasil
print(melted_tfidf)

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from scipy.spatial.distance import cosine


# Step 1: Mengubah DataFrame TF-IDF menjadi Format Wide
tfidf_wide = melted_tfidf.pivot(index='Sentence', columns='Term', values='TF-IDF').fillna(0)

# Step 2: Calculate cosine similarity between sentences
num_sentences = len(tfidf_wide)
adjacency_matrix = np.zeros((num_sentences, num_sentences))

for i in range(num_sentences):
    for j in range(i, num_sentences):  # Hanya menghitung segitiga atas
        if i == j:
            adjacency_matrix[i][j] = 1.0  # Kalimat sama dengan dirinya sendiri
        else:
            similarity = 1 - cosine(tfidf_wide.iloc[i], tfidf_wide.iloc[j])
            adjacency_matrix[i][j] = similarity
            adjacency_matrix[j][i] = similarity  # Matrix is symmetric

# Membuat DataFrame Adjacency Matrix
adjacency_df = pd.DataFrame(adjacency_matrix,
                            index=tfidf_wide.index,
                            columns=tfidf_wide.index)

# Menampilkan Adjacency Matrix
print("Adjacency Matrix:")
print(adjacency_df)

# Menyaring dengan Threshold (Opsional)
threshold = 0.5
adjacency_df_thresholded = adjacency_df.where(adjacency_df > threshold, 0)

print("\nAdjacency Matrix (with threshold):")
print(adjacency_df_thresholded)

# Optional: Save to CSV
adjacency_df.to_csv('adjacency_matrix.csv')
adjacency_df_thresholded.to_csv('adjacency_matrix_thresholded.csv')

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import networkx as nx
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity
import textwrap

# Hitung Cosine Similarity dan Simpan ke DataFrame
cosine_sim = cosine_similarity(tfidf_wide)

# menyimpan nilai similarity antar kalimat
similarity_df = pd.DataFrame(cosine_sim, index=tfidf_wide.index, columns=tfidf_wide.index)

# Membangun Graph dari Matriks Similarity
G = nx.from_pandas_adjacency(similarity_df)

# Remove self-loops
G.remove_edges_from(nx.selfloop_edges(G))

# Function to get the largest connected component
def get_largest_component(G):
    return max(nx.connected_components(G), key=len)

# Ensure the graph is connected
while not nx.is_connected(G):
    largest_component = get_largest_component(G)
    isolated_nodes = set(G.nodes()) - set(largest_component)
    if not isolated_nodes:
        break
    for node in isolated_nodes:
        similarities = [(other_node, similarity_df.loc[node, other_node])
                        for other_node in largest_component]
        most_similar_node = max(similarities, key=lambda x: x[1])[0]
        G.add_edge(node, most_similar_node)

# Fungsi Membungkus Teks untuk Label
def wrap_text(text, width=20):
    return '\n'.join(textwrap.wrap(text, width=width))

# Prepare labels (wrapped sentences)
labels = {node: wrap_text(node) for node in G.nodes()}

# visualize the graph
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 16))  # Increased figure size
pos = nx.spring_layout(G, k=0.5, iterations=50)

# Calculate node sizes based on degree centrality
degree_centrality = nx.degree_centrality(G)
node_sizes = [v * 10000 for v in degree_centrality.values()]  # Increased node sizes

# Draw the graph
nx.draw_networkx_nodes(G, pos, node_size=node_sizes, node_color='lightblue')
nx.draw_networkx_edges(G, pos, alpha=0.3)

# Add labels
nx.draw_networkx_labels(G, pos, labels, font_size=6)  # Reduced font size

plt.title("Connected Sentence Similarity Graph")
plt.axis('off')
plt.tight_layout()

# Save the graph as an image
plt.savefig('connected_sentence_similarity_graph.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')

# Show the plot
plt.show()

# Print some information about the graph
print(f"Number of nodes: {G.number_of_nodes()}")
print(f"Number of edges: {G.number_of_edges()}")
print(f"Is the graph connected? {nx.is_connected(G)}")

# Calculate centrality measures
closeness_centrality = nx.closeness_centrality(G)
betweenness_centrality = nx.betweenness_centrality(G)

# Create a DataFrame with centrality measures
centrality_data = []
for node in G.nodes():
    centrality_data.append({
        'Sentence': node,
        'Degree Centrality': degree_centrality[node],
        'Closeness Centrality': closeness_centrality[node],
        'Betweenness Centrality': betweenness_centrality[node]
    })

centrality_df = pd.DataFrame(centrality_data)

# Sort by Degree Centrality
centrality_df = centrality_df.sort_values('Degree Centrality', ascending=False)

print("\nCentrality Measures:")
print(centrality_df)

# Save centrality measures to CSV
centrality_df.to_csv('centrality_measures_with_sentences.csv', index=False)

# Optionally, print the top 5 sentences by each centrality measure
print("\nTop 5 sentences by Degree Centrality:")
print(centrality_df.nlargest(5, 'Degree Centrality')[['Sentence', 'Degree Centrality']])

print("\nTop 5 sentences by Closeness Centrality:")
print(centrality_df.nlargest(5, 'Closeness Centrality')[['Sentence', 'Closeness Centrality']])

print("\nTop 5 sentences by Betweenness Centrality:")
print(centrality_df.nlargest(5, 'Betweenness Centrality')[['Sentence', 'Betweenness Centrality']])
